          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Measurement of cross section for 24Na production from",
                "magnesium isotopes by 13.5-18.0 MeV neutrons"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "3POLIPJ"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " 3 MV Van de Graff of 25 micro-Ampere",
                "deuteron beam served as neutron source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The T-target in the form of titanium tritide was",
                "about 1.12 mg/cm**2 thick. Two deuteron energies were",
                "applied: 1.8 and 2.0 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Monoenergetic neutrons"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Enriched samples of MgO (Mg-25: 96.4+-0.3%,",
                "Mg-26: 97.1+-0.2%) and 99.99% Al foil were used.",
                "The weight of magnesium samples was around 70-80 mg",
                "and of Al foils was around 170 mg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "Powder samples of MgO were placed in perspex containers",
                "around which the Al standard-monitor foil was wrapped.",
                "The weight of magnesium samples and Al foils was chosen",
                "to achieve approximately equal dead-time and pile-up",
                "effects, during counting.",
                "After irradiation and ca. 5h decay the samples were",
                "counted with NaI(Tl) detector for 2000-4000 s. Since",
                "the 24Na-lines only were observed, the integral",
                "counting was performed within the gamma-energy range",
                "from 0.4-3.0 MeV.",
                "MgO sample and Al foil were activated simultaneously",
                "in the same position of the sample holder, were counted",
                "directly one after another to minimise instrumental",
                "errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 7.5*7.5 cm Na-I(Tl) detector"
              ]
            }
          ],
